12:54.074 --> 12:55.375
Passcode, shoot.

12:55.408 --> 12:57.044
Uh... uh, uh, uh, uh, uh.

12:57.077 --> 12:58.378
Jesus's birthday?

12:58.411 --> 13:00.380
12-25, no.

13:00.413 --> 13:02.582
Uh, last four of social?

13:02.615 --> 13:04.584
3-1-2-4, no.

13:04.617 --> 13:06.119
Valencia's birthday?

13:06.153 --> 13:08.521
Let's see, it's 5-5... 5-5-8-8.

13:08.555 --> 13:10.523
Yes! Oh, God,
he really loves her.

13:10.557 --> 13:12.392
Okay.

13:12.425 --> 13:14.527
Text messages.

13:14.561 --> 13:17.597
"Rebecca Bunch,"
ooh, that's a bad one.

13:17.630 --> 13:20.467
(sighs, chuckles)

13:20.500 --> 13:22.502
(sighs)

13:28.575 --> 13:30.577
(laughs with relief)

13:32.880 --> 13:34.882
*

13:38.085 --> 13:40.053
VANESSA:
* Don't smell the shirt

13:40.087 --> 13:43.223
* You're running out of time.

13:45.926 --> 13:47.594
All right.

13:58.005 --> 14:00.874
(sighs, chuckles)

14:04.211 --> 14:07.180
Honey, you heard
what Father Brah said.

14:07.214 --> 14:09.049
We need to really connect.

14:09.082 --> 14:10.283
Put the phone away.

14:10.317 --> 14:12.285
You're right.

14:12.319 --> 14:14.287
You're absolutely right.

14:14.321 --> 14:18.225
Okay, let's do this,
let's... connect.

14:22.029 --> 14:24.364
*

14:35.342 --> 14:37.344
(sighs)

14:37.377 --> 14:39.312
You blinked. I win. (laughs)

14:39.346 --> 14:40.948
I-I don't think that's what
we're supposed to be doing.

14:40.981 --> 14:42.549
I don't know what we're
supposed to be doing.

14:42.582 --> 14:45.218
Maybe we should hold hands.

14:45.252 --> 14:47.287
Okay.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.325
*

14:55.428 --> 14:56.930
You know, mine is really good.

14:56.964 --> 14:57.965
Do you want to try it?

14:57.998 --> 14:59.366
Sure.

14:59.399 --> 15:01.268
Uh, okay.

15:14.714 --> 15:16.316
(grunts)

15:21.321 --> 15:23.290
Mmm.

15:23.323 --> 15:24.291
This is nice.

15:24.324 --> 15:25.325
Yep.

15:27.327 --> 15:29.029
Josh.

15:29.062 --> 15:31.064
What are you...?

15:31.098 --> 15:33.266
Oh... my God,
thank God you're back.

15:33.300 --> 15:35.135
What's going on?

15:35.168 --> 15:36.436
Uh, how did you get in here?

15:36.469 --> 15:38.705
How does anyone get in anywhere?

15:38.738 --> 15:41.241
It's like we're there,
and then we're here.

15:41.274 --> 15:42.642
Aah, God.

15:42.675 --> 15:44.211
What?

15:44.244 --> 15:47.080
Okay, slow down,
slow down, slow down.

15:47.114 --> 15:48.281
Just slow down.

15:48.315 --> 15:53.320
Okay, uh, give me a second
to just get my story straight.

15:53.353 --> 15:54.687
Did you break in?

15:54.721 --> 15:56.689
(snaps)
Break-in, yes,
there was a break-in.

15:56.723 --> 15:59.292
But not here,
not here, never here.

15:59.326 --> 16:01.161
What?
Okay.

16:01.194 --> 16:03.696
So I was in my, uh, apartment,

16:03.730 --> 16:06.366
and, uh, somebody did
the thing that you...

16:06.399 --> 16:07.734
you were just saying, the thing
that you were just saying.

16:07.767 --> 16:09.302
They broke in?
Yes.

16:09.336 --> 16:11.171
Yes, you're so good.
We should have a charades night.

16:11.204 --> 16:12.272
Okay, Rebecca...
I haven't seen anyone
since the beach.

16:12.305 --> 16:14.774
Rebecca, wait, wait, someone
broke into your house?

16:14.807 --> 16:18.711
Yes, yes, they broke in,
and, um, they-they smashed it,

16:18.745 --> 16:21.248
uh, with a big...

16:21.281 --> 16:22.315
Rock.
Yes.

16:22.349 --> 16:23.316
You're so good at this.

16:23.350 --> 16:24.317
We should do teams of two.

16:24.351 --> 16:25.318
When are you next free?

16:25.352 --> 16:26.319
Wait, wait,
Rebecca, Rebecca.

16:26.353 --> 16:27.487
Just hold
yourself together.

16:27.520 --> 16:29.289
Did you call the police?

16:29.322 --> 16:30.757
No, no, no cops.

16:30.790 --> 16:32.459
No, didn't call the police.

16:32.492 --> 16:33.426
So why are you here?

16:33.460 --> 16:35.195
Slow down!

16:35.228 --> 16:36.229
Okay, so after
I couldn't reach you,

16:36.263 --> 16:37.464
I came here to be with you
and your girlfriend.

16:37.497 --> 16:38.465
All right, all right, all right.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.400
So take a deep breath.
Okay.

16:40.433 --> 16:42.735
I'm gonna say this
as slowly as possible.

16:42.769 --> 16:43.736
Okay.

16:43.770 --> 16:46.773
Okay, so someone used a rock

16:46.806 --> 16:51.444
and broke into your apartment?

16:51.478 --> 16:53.313
Was-was anything taken?

16:53.346 --> 16:55.348
No. No, just the rock
through the window.

16:55.382 --> 16:57.484
So I was scared,
and I came here,

16:57.517 --> 17:00.353
and the door was unlocked.

17:00.387 --> 17:01.621
Oh, man.

17:01.654 --> 17:03.723
I mean, you know,
I do that sometimes.

17:03.756 --> 17:06.326
(scoffs) Did I leave
the fridge open, too?

17:06.358 --> 17:10.063
Yes, you did, and I closed it,
and I saved a lot of cold cuts.

17:10.097 --> 17:12.398
Geez. Uh, you know what,
thank you.

17:12.432 --> 17:15.734
L-Look, okay,
you're really upset.

17:15.768 --> 17:18.271
Yeah, I-I am really upset.

17:18.305 --> 17:20.740
You know what, I'm probably...
I'm probably overreacting.

17:20.772 --> 17:23.276
It's not a big deal.
I'm gonna get out of your hair.

17:25.744 --> 17:26.779
Wait.

17:26.813 --> 17:28.715
Yeah?

17:29.716 --> 17:32.385
I don't feel okay about this.

17:32.419 --> 17:33.853
You don't?

17:33.886 --> 17:35.388
Of course not.

17:35.422 --> 17:36.389
Look at you.

17:36.423 --> 17:39.459
I can't send you home alone.

17:39.492 --> 17:40.627
Look how scared you are.

17:42.662 --> 17:45.332
You look like a tiny
scared little bird.

17:45.365 --> 17:46.799
(baby voice):
I do?

17:46.833 --> 17:48.535
(chuckles)

17:48.568 --> 17:50.870
Josh, I, um...

17:50.903 --> 17:53.540
I'm so sorry that I just
came in your house.

17:53.573 --> 17:54.874
No. No, it's okay,
you were scared.

17:54.907 --> 17:57.877
Look, why don't we go
back to your place,

17:57.910 --> 17:59.479
and I'll make sure
it's all okay.

17:59.512 --> 18:02.482
Thank you, Josh.

18:02.515 --> 18:04.351
I'm not scared anymore.

18:04.384 --> 18:06.419
And we'll get that broken
window fixed, right?

18:06.453 --> 18:09.422
Mmm, broken window.

18:09.456 --> 18:11.558
Broken window.

18:11.591 --> 18:13.560
Yes...

18:13.593 --> 18:14.661
Yes.

18:14.694 --> 18:16.429
Cool, let me just change.

18:16.463 --> 18:18.565
Great, and, hey, shower
if you're feeling it.

18:18.598 --> 18:19.566
No rush.

18:19.599 --> 18:21.801
It's really... really no rush.

18:21.834 --> 18:23.303
(door closes)

18:23.336 --> 18:26.573
God, Paula, I hope
your marriage is fixed by now.

18:28.675 --> 18:30.177
(groans)

18:30.210 --> 18:32.179
Ugh, just push it through.

18:32.212 --> 18:33.513
No, no, we can save
the cork.

18:33.546 --> 18:34.547
No, we can't.

18:34.581 --> 18:35.682
Be realistic, okay?

18:35.715 --> 18:37.550
We just got to push
the cork through

18:37.584 --> 18:40.553
and drink the wine with dirty
little pieces of cork in it.

18:40.587 --> 18:42.855
Is it great?
No, but that's life.

18:44.424 --> 18:45.525
(cell phone rings)

18:45.558 --> 18:47.394
I am not going to answer that.

18:47.427 --> 18:49.662
Nope.

18:49.696 --> 18:52.699
I just hope it doesn't have
something to do with the kids.

18:52.732 --> 18:54.834
They're upstairs.

18:54.867 --> 18:56.836
That's right.

18:56.869 --> 18:59.539
And you know how much trouble
they can get into upstairs.

18:59.572 --> 19:02.775
I'm just gonna check,
just for peace of mind.

19:04.811 --> 19:06.446
Oh, it's my mom.

19:06.479 --> 19:07.447
Something must be wrong.

19:07.480 --> 19:09.449
It's so late up in Buffalo.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.784
Her-her gout must be
bothering her.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.320
Mom, everything okay?

19:13.353 --> 19:14.621
Joints flaring up?

19:14.654 --> 19:17.624
Hi. So, okay, Josh caught me
coming in his house,

19:17.657 --> 19:19.492
and I started panicking,

19:19.526 --> 19:20.827
and I told him that
we'd be good at charades,

19:20.860 --> 19:22.362
and now he's being all
protective and masculine--

19:22.395 --> 19:23.496
he smells like karate,
and I love it--

19:23.530 --> 19:25.198
and he's getting dressed now,

19:25.232 --> 19:27.200
so what I need you to do is
I need you to go to my house,

19:27.234 --> 19:28.668
stop what you're doing,
and throw a rock

19:28.701 --> 19:30.570
through my sliding
glass door right now, okay?

19:32.539 --> 19:33.640
Copy that.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.975
Did you say "copy that"
to your mom?

19:36.008 --> 19:39.979
Yes, I have to make copies
for her health insurance.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.382
Okay, yeah, that's enough.

19:42.415 --> 19:43.883
Who calls you all the time?

19:43.916 --> 19:44.884
You think I haven't noticed?

19:44.917 --> 19:46.553
What's really going on?

19:46.586 --> 19:47.620
I don't have time
for this, Scott, okay?

19:47.654 --> 19:48.688
I got to go.

19:48.721 --> 19:49.889
I'll be back in
an hour, tops.

19:49.922 --> 19:51.891
It's the peewee football coach,
isn't it?

19:51.924 --> 19:53.560
I see him coming back
for seconds

19:53.593 --> 19:55.328
when you bring
the orange slices.

19:55.362 --> 19:56.663
Oh, my God, no.

19:56.696 --> 19:58.265
Scott, uh, look, I have to go.

19:58.298 --> 20:00.600
Paula, if you walk
out that door without me,

20:00.633 --> 20:03.270
you're rocking the boat
in the bad way. Big time.

20:03.303 --> 20:04.737
Ugh, fine.

20:04.771 --> 20:06.273
Come with me then, okay?

20:06.306 --> 20:09.742
But you... you cannot
ask any questions, okay?

20:09.776 --> 20:11.778
*

20:14.781 --> 20:17.750
All right, let's go clean up
some broken glass.

20:17.784 --> 20:20.887
Hey, uh, first, can I just
get a glass of water?

20:20.920 --> 20:22.355
Uh, sure.
Thanks.

20:22.389 --> 20:24.757
And, uh, a toast
with almond butter?

20:24.791 --> 20:28.695
And a sliced apple cut
into very tiny slices.

20:28.728 --> 20:30.430
*

20:37.604 --> 20:39.038
(Scott groaning)

20:39.071 --> 20:41.040
I know I'm not supposed
to ask any questions,

20:41.073 --> 20:42.909
but can I ask what
you're looking for?

20:42.942 --> 20:44.911
Yeah, I need a rock,
like, a nice-sized one.

20:44.944 --> 20:45.912
Can I help you look?

20:45.945 --> 20:48.047
Uh, okay sure.

20:48.080 --> 20:49.616
I mean, uh, if you want to.

20:49.649 --> 20:50.617
Awesome.

20:50.650 --> 20:52.619
(groans)

20:52.652 --> 20:53.953
First I got to
use the bathroom.

20:53.986 --> 20:55.021
You know how my body
deals with excitement.

20:55.054 --> 20:56.889
Okay, use the sliding glass
door, it's always open.

20:56.923 --> 20:57.890
But hurry up, okay?

20:57.924 --> 20:59.592
Be right back.

21:02.462 --> 21:03.930
(cell phone chimes)

21:05.832 --> 21:08.368
Oh, God, I just need a rock.

21:08.401 --> 21:09.469
I hate Southern California!

21:09.502 --> 21:11.738
No rocks, no dirt, no sticks!

21:11.771 --> 21:13.373
(huffing)

21:13.406 --> 21:15.408
Paula, look.

21:15.442 --> 21:16.509
(gasps)

21:16.543 --> 21:18.077
Oh, my God, babe,
it's beautiful.

21:18.110 --> 21:19.679
It's textbook.

21:19.712 --> 21:20.813
It's like the image you get

21:20.847 --> 21:22.415
when you Google the word "rock."

21:22.449 --> 21:24.050
(chuckles)
Now what do we do?

21:24.083 --> 21:25.385
Go, go, go, go, go!

21:25.418 --> 21:26.319
Go, go!

21:26.353 --> 21:27.687
Go, go, go, go, go!

21:27.720 --> 21:29.356
Chuck it!

21:29.389 --> 21:30.222
What?

21:30.256 --> 21:31.524
Scott, throw it
through the window.

21:31.558 --> 21:32.759
I can't throw it--

21:32.792 --> 21:33.960
Scott, the boat is sinking.

21:33.993 --> 21:35.762
Throw the rock
through the widow!
(shouts)

21:39.899 --> 21:42.369
(dogs barking)

21:42.402 --> 21:43.703
(laughs)
(whoops)

21:43.736 --> 21:44.971
I can't believe
we did that.

21:45.004 --> 21:46.973
Uh, what else can we break?

21:47.006 --> 21:48.541
Oh, I still got to pee!

21:48.575 --> 21:50.910
(both laughing)

21:53.480 --> 21:55.448
So, I just want to let you
know I was thinking about it

21:55.482 --> 21:57.450
in the car and what if the
bad guys felt really bad

21:57.484 --> 21:58.685
about what they'd done
and-and they and they went

21:58.718 --> 22:00.720
and cleaned it up, 'cause I've
heard about that happening.

22:00.753 --> 22:03.423
Oh, my gosh, that's--

22:03.456 --> 22:04.424
I shouldn't be surprised,

22:04.457 --> 22:05.525
because that's
the way I left it.

22:05.558 --> 22:06.659
Yeah, that's broken glass.

22:06.693 --> 22:07.694
That's a lot of broken glass.

22:07.727 --> 22:09.429
Yeah, that's a legitimate...

22:09.462 --> 22:10.563
Wow.
It's a legitimate mess.

22:10.597 --> 22:12.365
Well, I mean,
this is really creepy.

22:12.399 --> 22:13.833
But at least you're not hurt.

22:13.866 --> 22:15.134
That's the
most important thing.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.136
Is it?

22:17.169 --> 22:17.970
Of course!

22:18.004 --> 22:20.039
You can always
replace a door, but,

22:20.072 --> 22:21.741
you know,
there's only one Becks.

22:23.175 --> 22:26.513
Oh, well, there's
only one Josh Chan.

22:26.546 --> 22:28.147
Actually, there's a lot
of Josh Chans.

22:28.180 --> 22:29.449
There's one in Azusa.

22:29.482 --> 22:31.384
Yeah, I used to play him
in soccer.

22:31.418 --> 22:32.419
(both chuckle)

22:32.452 --> 22:33.886
Wow, um,

22:33.920 --> 22:35.522
I feel

22:35.555 --> 22:37.390
really rattled.

22:37.424 --> 22:38.525
I need some wine.

22:38.558 --> 22:39.426
Do you want some wine?

22:39.459 --> 22:40.593
You know what? Sure.

22:40.627 --> 22:41.894
Let's do it.
Great.

22:41.928 --> 22:43.530
Uh, oh, can I have ice in mine?

22:43.563 --> 22:45.632
Yeah, okay, iced wine.

22:45.665 --> 22:47.567
Coming up.

22:47.600 --> 22:50.136
And then we'll
clean up some glass.

22:50.169 --> 22:51.404
Okay.

22:51.438 --> 22:52.171
Oh, yeah, here you go.

22:52.204 --> 22:53.473
Let me get that.

22:53.506 --> 22:55.708
Oh, thank you.

22:55.742 --> 22:57.076
Hey, um,

22:57.109 --> 22:59.178
I feel really safe
with you here.

22:59.211 --> 23:00.413
Thank you.

23:00.447 --> 23:01.681
(scoffs) Of course.

23:01.714 --> 23:03.182
It's the least I can do.

23:03.215 --> 23:06.419
Thank you.

23:06.453 --> 23:07.820
Hey.

23:07.854 --> 23:09.055
You know,
I'm thinking out loud.

23:09.088 --> 23:11.057
As-as long as
we're having wine--

23:11.090 --> 23:13.493
Oh, cheers, by the way. Eyes.

23:13.526 --> 23:14.594
There we go.

23:14.627 --> 23:15.828
Um, I'm pretty hungry.

23:15.862 --> 23:17.129
Do-do you want to get some food?

23:17.163 --> 23:19.131
There's a great fondue place
that-that delivers

23:19.165 --> 23:20.433
right around the corner.

23:20.467 --> 23:21.568
Sounds great.
I've never had it.

23:21.601 --> 23:22.735
Great.

23:22.769 --> 23:24.504
(laughs)
God...

23:25.705 --> 23:27.206
You've really just turned
this night around for me.

23:27.239 --> 23:28.641
Ah...

23:28.675 --> 23:30.710
You know, I was so scared

23:30.743 --> 23:32.712
but now, um,

23:32.745 --> 23:34.213
I just feel like
a piece of bread

23:34.246 --> 23:35.882
in a warm bath of cheese.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.149
Hmm.

23:37.183 --> 23:38.184
That's fondue.

23:38.217 --> 23:39.218
I'm describing fondue.

23:39.251 --> 23:40.152
Oh, gotcha.

23:40.186 --> 23:41.988
Yeah, I thought
it was some kind of soup.

23:42.021 --> 23:43.089
No! I'm sorry.

23:43.122 --> 23:44.624
That was confusing.
That was my bad.

23:44.657 --> 23:46.493
(doorbell rings)

23:46.526 --> 23:48.227
Hmm, that's weird.
I'm not expecting anybody.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.663
Oh, it's probably the cops.

23:50.697 --> 23:51.731
Cops-- Sorry, hmm?

23:51.764 --> 23:52.865
Josh?

23:52.899 --> 23:53.666
You called the cops?

23:53.700 --> 23:54.701
Of course I did.

23:54.734 --> 23:55.802
No, no, but Josh, Josh,

23:55.835 --> 23:57.003
J-Josh, you know what they say.

23:57.036 --> 23:58.538
Snitches get stitches.

23:58.571 --> 23:59.872
Come on in, Officer.

23:59.906 --> 24:01.674
I got a call about
the attempted burglary?

24:01.708 --> 24:03.976
You know what?
The-the glass is just smashed.

24:04.010 --> 24:05.578
They smashed the whole door.

24:05.612 --> 24:06.913
Don't worry, I'm here now.

24:06.946 --> 24:08.481
And rest assured, ma'am,

24:08.515 --> 24:10.750
I won't stop till I get
to the bottom of this.

24:10.783 --> 24:11.784
(sighs)

24:17.757 --> 24:19.225
When did the incident occur?

24:19.258 --> 24:20.727
You know, no idea.

24:20.760 --> 24:21.994
I, uh, it was like this
when I got home.

24:22.028 --> 24:23.530
Why didn't you call the police

24:23.563 --> 24:24.764
when you first
discovered the window?

24:24.797 --> 24:25.865
I panicked, you know?

24:25.898 --> 24:27.033
I just,
I-I-I freaked out.

24:27.066 --> 24:28.200
And I just, I fled.

24:28.234 --> 24:29.602
"Fled"?

24:29.636 --> 24:30.870
Yeah, slow down!

24:30.903 --> 24:32.038
JOSH:
Okay, okay, just tell him

24:32.071 --> 24:33.873
what you know, Becks.

24:33.906 --> 24:36.609
She can't follow
if you talk too fast.

24:37.777 --> 24:39.879
Okay.

24:39.912 --> 24:41.914
Whew.

24:41.948 --> 24:43.916
So what happened

24:43.950 --> 24:45.752
is my friend, Josh Chan,

24:45.785 --> 24:48.688
called you because...

24:48.721 --> 24:50.523
he is so protective of me.

24:50.557 --> 24:52.058
Bless him.
But I understand

24:52.091 --> 24:53.726
that this is not really
worth your time.

24:53.760 --> 24:55.261
And the reason for that

24:55.294 --> 24:56.829
I will go into right now.

24:56.863 --> 24:58.798
All right, as I look

24:58.831 --> 24:59.699
at this crime scene,

24:59.732 --> 25:01.734
there appears to be
no evidence of theft

25:01.768 --> 25:04.804
or any sign that someone entered
the apartment at all.

25:04.837 --> 25:07.874
Let's take a closer look at
the shards of glass, shall we?

25:07.907 --> 25:10.009
Now, when I look at these
shards of glass,

25:10.042 --> 25:12.011
there is also no evidence
of secondary compression

25:12.044 --> 25:14.881
by a shoe or shoes,
to use the plural.

25:14.914 --> 25:16.683
So I think we
can safely say

25:16.716 --> 25:18.017
